.Dd $Mdocdate: March 25 2023 $
.Dt RUNPTY 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm runpty
.Nd execute commands in a new pty
.\" .Sh LIBRARY
.\" For sections 2, 3, and 9 only.
.\" Not used in OpenBSD.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar command
.Op Ar args
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility executes the given
.Ar command
with a new pty
.Pq pseudo-terminal
as the controlling terminal.
.Pp
Executing the command in a new pty mitigates the command from using
.Xr ioctl 2 Ns 's
like
.Dv TIOCSTI
and
.Dv TIOCLINUX
which can be used to execute commands in the shell of the controlling terminal.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr ioctl 2 ,
.Xr ioctl_tty 2 ,
.Xr pty 7
